place.name: WEST TOFTS
place.gazetteerText: TOFTS (West), a parish in Thetford district, Norfolk; 5 miles NE of Brandon r. station. Post town, Brandon. Acres, 3,051. Real property, £1,138. Pop., 193. Houses, 36. The property is not much divided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £200. Patron, Sir J. Sutton, Bart. The church is partly new and all good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
